      <title>Getting Things Ready</title>
      <para>In order for you to work with the games in this book, you'll need a few things set up. This chapter will help you get started.</para>
      
      <sect1 xml:id="sec.Installing.Ruby">
        <title>Installing Ruby</title>

        <sect2 xml:id="sec.rb.Windows">
          <title>Windows</title>
          <para>Download and install the Ruby Installer for Windows - <link xlink:href="http://rubyforge.org/frs/download.php/69034/rubyinstaller-1.8.7-p249-rc2.exe" />.</para>
           
        </sect2>
        
        <sect2 xml:id="sec.rb.Mac">
          <title>Mac</title>
          <para>If you have a Mac with Leopard or Snow Leopard, you already have everything you need to begin programming, as Ruby is already installed.</para>
        </sect2>
        
        <sect2 xml:id="sec.rb.Ubuntu">
          <title>Ubuntu</title>
          <para>On Ubuntu, Ruby can be installed with</para>
            <para><command>sudo apt-get install ruby-full</command></para>
        </sect2>

	<sect2 xml:id="sec.rb.Gentoo">
          <title>Gentoo</title>
	  <para>On Gentoo, Ruby can be installed with</para>
	    <para><command>sudo emerge dev-lang/ruby</command></para>
	</sect2>

      </sect1>

